<p><b>Breakbeat</b> (sometimes <b>breakbeats</b> or <b>breaks</b>) is a term used to describe a collection of sub-<a href="/wiki/Music_genre" title="Music genre">genres</a> of <a href="/wiki/Electronic_music" title="Electronic music">electronic music</a>, usually characterized by the use of a non-straightened 4/4 drum pattern (as opposed to the steady beat of <a href="/wiki/House_music" title="House music">house</a> or <a href="/wiki/Trance_music" title="Trance music">trance</a>). These rhythms may be characterised by their intensive use of <a href="/wiki/Syncopation" title="Syncopation">syncopation</a> and <a href="/wiki/Polyrhythms" title="Polyrhythms" class="mw-redirect">polyrhythms</a>.</p>
